; Regression test for issue #771: --explicit not working if there are no pre-declarations (BZ#771)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/771
;
; The --explicit flag was intended to require pre-declared accounts, but would silently
; skip checking when NO account directives existed in the file. The check now works
; correctly via --strict (warnings) and --pedantic (errors) regardless of whether any
; accounts are pre-declared.
;
; Note: --explicit is now a no-op; --strict is the working replacement.

2024/01/01 Test
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

test bal --strict
             $-10.00  Assets:Cash
              $10.00  Expenses:Food
--------------------
                   0
__ERROR__
Warning: "$FILE", line 12: Unknown account 'Expenses:Food'
Warning: "$FILE", line 12: Unknown commodity '$'
Warning: "$FILE", line 13: Unknown account 'Assets:Cash'
end test
